00923 );
00924 static PyObject *Vector_angle(VectorObject *self, PyObject *args)
00925 {
00926     const int size = MIN2(self->size, 3); /* 4D angle makes no sense */
00927     float tvec[MAX_DIMENSIONS];

00930     int x;

00934         return NULL;

00937         return NULL;
00938

00940      * even though n this case 'w' is ignored */

00952         dot_other += (double)tvec[x]      * (double)tvec[x];
00953         dot       += (double)self->vec[x] * (double)tvec[x];

01330 /* sequence slice (get): vector[a:b] */
01331 static PyObject *Vector_slice(VectorObject *self, int begin, int end)
01332 {
01333     PyObject *tuple;
01334     int count;
01335 
01336     if (BaseMath_ReadCallback(self) == -1)
01337         return NULL;
01338 
01339     CLAMP(begin, 0, self->size);
01340     if (end < 0) end = self->size + end + 1;
01341     CLAMP(end, 0, self->size);
01342     begin = MIN2(begin, end);
01343 
01344     tuple = PyTuple_New(end - begin);
01345     for (count = begin; count < end; count++) {
01346         PyTuple_SET_ITEM(tuple, count - begin, PyFloat_FromDouble(self->vec[count]));
01347     }
01348 
01349     return tuple;
01350 }
01351 /* sequence slice (set): vector[a:b] = value */
01352 static int Vector_ass_slice(VectorObject *self, int begin, int end, PyObject *seq)
01353 {
01354     int size = 0;
01355     float *vec = NULL;
01356 
01357     if (BaseMath_ReadCallback(self) == -1)
01358         return -1;
01359 
01360     CLAMP(begin, 0, self->size);
01361     CLAMP(end, 0, self->size);
01362     begin = MIN2(begin, end);
01363 
01364     size = (end - begin);
01365     if (mathutils_array_parse_alloc(&vec, size, seq, "vector[begin:end] = [...]") == -1) {
01366         goto cleanup;
01367     }
01368 
01369     if (vec == NULL) {
01370         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_MemoryError,
01371                         "vec[:] = seq: "
01372                         "problem allocating pointer space");
01373         return -1;
01374     }
01375 
01376     /*parsed well - now set in vector*/
01377     memcpy(self->vec + begin, vec, size * sizeof(float));
01378 
01379     if (BaseMath_WriteCallback(self) == -1)
01380         return -1;
01381 
01382     PyMem_Free(vec);
01383 
01384     return 0;
01385 
01386 cleanup:
01387     PyMem_Free(vec);
01388     return -1;
01389 }

01541 /* COLUMN VECTOR Multiplication (Matrix X Vector)
01542  * [1][4][7]   [a]
01543  * [2][5][8] * [b]
01544  * [3][6][9]   [c]
01545  *
01546  * note: vector/matrix multiplication IS NOT COMMUTATIVE!!!!
01547  * note: assume read callbacks have been done first.
01548  */
01549 int column_vector_multiplication(float r_vec[MAX_DIMENSIONS], VectorObject *vec, MatrixObject *mat)
01550 {
01551     float vec_cpy[MAX_DIMENSIONS];
01552     int row, col, z = 0;
01553 
01554     if (mat->num_col != vec->size) {
01555         if (mat->num_col == 4 && vec->size == 3) {
01556             vec_cpy[3] = 1.0f;
01557         }
01558         else {
01559             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
01560                             "matrix * vector: "
01561                             "len(matrix.col) and len(vector) must be the same, "
01562                             "except for 4x4 matrix * 3D vector.");
01563             return -1;
01564         }
01565     }
01566 
01567     memcpy(vec_cpy, vec->vec, vec->size * sizeof(float));
01568 
01569     r_vec[3] = 1.0f;
01570 
01571     for (row = 0; row < mat->num_row; row++) {
01572         double dot = 0.0f;
01573         for (col = 0; col < mat->num_col; col++) {
01574             dot += (double)(MATRIX_ITEM(mat, row, col) * vec_cpy[col]);
01575         }
01576         r_vec[z++] = (float)dot;
01577     }
01578 
01579     return 0;
01580 }

01597 static PyObject *Vector_mul(PyObject *v1, PyObject *v2)
01598 {
01599     VectorObject *vec1 = NULL, *vec2 = NULL;
01600     float scalar;
01601     int vec_size;
01602 
01603     if (VectorObject_Check(v1)) {
01604         vec1 = (VectorObject *)v1;
01605         if (BaseMath_ReadCallback(vec1) == -1)
01606             return NULL;
01607     }
01608     if (VectorObject_Check(v2)) {
01609         vec2 = (VectorObject *)v2;
01610         if (BaseMath_ReadCallback(vec2) == -1)
01611             return NULL;
01612     }
01613 
01614 
01615     /* make sure v1 is always the vector */
01616     if (vec1 && vec2) {
01617         if (vec1->size != vec2->size) {
01618             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
01619                             "Vector multiplication: "
01620                             "vectors must have the same dimensions for this operation");
01621             return NULL;
01622         }
01623 
01624         /*dot product*/
01625         return PyFloat_FromDouble(dot_vn_vn(vec1->vec, vec2->vec, vec1->size));
01626     }
01627     else if (vec1) {
01628         if (MatrixObject_Check(v2)) {
01629             /* VEC * MATRIX */
01630             float tvec[MAX_DIMENSIONS];
01631 
01632             if (BaseMath_ReadCallback((MatrixObject *)v2) == -1)
01633                 return NULL;
01634             if (row_vector_multiplication(tvec, vec1, (MatrixObject *)v2) == -1) {
01635                 return NULL;
01636             }
01637 
01638             if (((MatrixObject *)v2)->num_row == 4 && vec1->size == 3) {
01639                 vec_size = 3;
01640             }
01641             else {
01642                 vec_size = ((MatrixObject *)v2)->num_col;
01643             }
01644 
01645             return Vector_CreatePyObject(tvec, vec_size, Py_NEW, Py_TYPE(vec1));
01646         }
01647         else if (QuaternionObject_Check(v2)) {
01648             /* VEC * QUAT */
01649 /* ------ to be removed ------*/
01650 #if 1
01651             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
01652                             "(Vector * Quat) is now removed, reverse the "
01653                             "order (promoted to an Error for Debug builds)");
01654             return NULL;
01655 #else
01656             QuaternionObject *quat2 = (QuaternionObject *)v2;
01657             float tvec[3];
01658 
01659             if (vec1->size != 3) {
01660                 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
01661                                 "Vector multiplication: "
01662                                 "only 3D vector rotations (with quats) currently supported");
01663                 return NULL;
01664             }
01665             if (BaseMath_ReadCallback(quat2) == -1) {
01666                 return NULL;
01667             }
01668 
01669             copy_v3_v3(tvec, vec1->vec);
01670             mul_qt_v3(quat2->quat, tvec);
01671             return Vector_CreatePyObject(tvec, 3, Py_NEW, Py_TYPE(vec1));
01672 #endif
01673 /* ------ to be removed ------*/
01674         }
01675         else if (((scalar = PyFloat_AsDouble(v2)) == -1.0f && PyErr_Occurred()) == 0) { /* VEC * FLOAT */
01676             return vector_mul_float(vec1, scalar);
01677         }
01678     }
01679     else if (vec2) {
01680         if (((scalar = PyFloat_AsDouble(v1)) == -1.0f && PyErr_Occurred()) == 0) { /* FLOAT * VEC */
01681             return vector_mul_float(vec2, scalar);
01682         }
01683     }
01684     else {
01685         BLI_assert(!"internal error");
01686     }
01687 
01688     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01689                  "Vector multiplication: "
01690                  "not supported between '%.200s' and '%.200s' types",
01691                  Py_TYPE(v1)->tp_name, Py_TYPE(v2)->tp_name);
01692     return NULL;
01693 }

01871 /*------------------------tp_richcmpr
01872  * returns -1 execption, 0 false, 1 true */
01873 static PyObject *Vector_richcmpr(PyObject *objectA, PyObject *objectB, int comparison_type)
01874 {
01875     VectorObject *vecA = NULL, *vecB = NULL;
01876     int result = 0;
01877     double epsilon = .000001f;
01878     double lenA, lenB;
01879 
01880     if (!VectorObject_Check(objectA) || !VectorObject_Check(objectB)) {
01881         if (comparison_type == Py_NE) {
01882             Py_RETURN_TRUE;
01883         }
01884         else {
01885             Py_RETURN_FALSE;
01886         }
01887     }
01888     vecA = (VectorObject *)objectA;
01889     vecB = (VectorObject *)objectB;
01890 
01891     if (BaseMath_ReadCallback(vecA) == -1 || BaseMath_ReadCallback(vecB) == -1)
01892         return NULL;
01893 
01894     if (vecA->size != vecB->size) {
01895         if (comparison_type == Py_NE) {
01896             Py_RETURN_TRUE;
01897         }
01898         else {
01899             Py_RETURN_FALSE;
01900         }
01901     }
01902 
01903     switch (comparison_type) {
01904         case Py_LT:
01905             lenA = vec_magnitude_nosqrt(vecA->vec, vecA->size);
01906             lenB = vec_magnitude_nosqrt(vecB->vec, vecB->size);
01907             if (lenA < lenB) {
01908                 result = 1;
01909             }
01910             break;
01911         case Py_LE:
01912             lenA = vec_magnitude_nosqrt(vecA->vec, vecA->size);
01913             lenB = vec_magnitude_nosqrt(vecB->vec, vecB->size);
01914             if (lenA < lenB) {
01915                 result = 1;
01916             }
01917             else {
01918                 result = (((lenA + epsilon) > lenB) && ((lenA - epsilon) < lenB));
01919             }
01920             break;
01921         case Py_EQ:
01922             result = EXPP_VectorsAreEqual(vecA->vec, vecB->vec, vecA->size, 1);
01923             break;
01924         case Py_NE:
01925             result = !EXPP_VectorsAreEqual(vecA->vec, vecB->vec, vecA->size, 1);
01926             break;
01927         case Py_GT:
01928             lenA = vec_magnitude_nosqrt(vecA->vec, vecA->size);
01929             lenB = vec_magnitude_nosqrt(vecB->vec, vecB->size);
01930             if (lenA > lenB) {
01931                 result = 1;
01932             }
01933             break;
01934         case Py_GE:
01935             lenA = vec_magnitude_nosqrt(vecA->vec, vecA->size);
01936             lenB = vec_magnitude_nosqrt(vecB->vec, vecB->size);
01937             if (lenA > lenB) {
01938                 result = 1;
01939             }
01940             else {
01941                 result = (((lenA + epsilon) > lenB) && ((lenA - epsilon) < lenB));
01942             }
01943             break;
01944         default:
01945             printf("The result of the comparison could not be evaluated");
01946             break;
01947     }
01948     if (result == 1) {
01949         Py_RETURN_TRUE;
01950     }
01951     else {
01952         Py_RETURN_FALSE;
01953     }
01954 }

01971 {
01972     if (PyIndex_Check(item)) {
01973         Py_ssize_t i;
01974         i = PyNumber_AsSsize_t(item, PyExc_IndexError);
01975         if (i == -1 && PyErr_Occurred())
01976             return NULL;
01977         if (i < 0)
01978             i += self->size;
01979         return Vector_item(self, i);
01980     }
01981     else if (PySlice_Check(item)) {
01982         Py_ssize_t start, stop, step, slicelength;
01983 
01984         if (PySlice_GetIndicesEx((void *)item, self->size, &start, &stop, &step, &slicelength) < 0)
01985             return NULL;
01986 
01987         if (slicelength <= 0) {
01988             return PyTuple_New(0);
01989         }
01990         else if (step == 1) {
01991             return Vector_slice(self, start, stop);
01992         }
01993         else {
01994             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_IndexError,
01995                             "slice steps not supported with vectors");
01996             return NULL;
01997         }
01998     }
01999     else {
02000         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
02001                      "vector indices must be integers, not %.200s",
02002                      Py_TYPE(item)->tp_name);
02003         return NULL;
02004     }
02005 }

02115 static int Vector_length_set(VectorObject *self, PyObject *value)
02116 {
02117     double dot = 0.0f, param;
02118 
02119     if (BaseMath_ReadCallback(self) == -1)
02120         return -1;
02121 
02122     if ((param = PyFloat_AsDouble(value)) == -1.0 && PyErr_Occurred()) {
02123         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
02124                         "length must be set to a number");
02125         return -1;
02126     }
02127 
02128     if (param < 0.0) {
02129         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
02130                         "cannot set a vectors length to a negative value");
02131         return -1;
02132     }
02133     if (param == 0.0) {
02134         fill_vn_fl(self->vec, self->size, 0.0f);
02135         return 0;
02136     }
02137 
02138     dot = dot_vn_vn(self->vec, self->vec, self->size);
02139 
02140     if (!dot) /* cant sqrt zero */
02141         return 0;
02142 
02143     dot = sqrt(dot);
02144 
02145     if (dot == param)
02146         return 0;
02147 
02148     dot = dot / param;
02149 
02150     mul_vn_fl(self->vec, self->size, 1.0 / dot);
02151 
02152     (void)BaseMath_WriteCallback(self); /* checked already */
02153 
02154     return 0;
02155 }

02169 /* Get a new Vector according to the provided swizzle. This function has little
02170  * error checking, as we are in control of the inputs: the closure is set by us
02171  * in Vector_createSwizzleGetSeter. */
02172 static PyObject *Vector_swizzle_get(VectorObject *self, void *closure)
02173 {
02174     size_t axis_to;
02175     size_t axis_from;
02176     float vec[MAX_DIMENSIONS];
02177     unsigned int swizzleClosure;
02178 
02179     if (BaseMath_ReadCallback(self) == -1)
02180         return NULL;
02181 
02182     /* Unpack the axes from the closure into an array. */
02183     axis_to = 0;
02184     swizzleClosure = GET_INT_FROM_POINTER(closure);
02185     while (swizzleClosure & SWIZZLE_VALID_AXIS) {
02186         axis_from = swizzleClosure & SWIZZLE_AXIS;
02187         if (axis_from >= self->size) {
02188             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError,
02189                             "Vector swizzle: "
02190                             "specified axis not present");
02191             return NULL;
02192         }
02193 
02194         vec[axis_to] = self->vec[axis_from];
02195         swizzleClosure = swizzleClosure >> SWIZZLE_BITS_PER_AXIS;
02196         axis_to++;
02197     }
02198 
02199     return Vector_CreatePyObject(vec, axis_to, Py_NEW, Py_TYPE(self));
02200 }

02202 /* Set the items of this vector using a swizzle.
02203  * - If value is a vector or list this operates like an array copy, except that
02204  *   the destination is effectively re-ordered as defined by the swizzle. At
02205  *   most min(len(source), len(dest)) values will be copied.
02206  * - If the value is scalar, it is copied to all axes listed in the swizzle.
02207  * - If an axis appears more than once in the swizzle, the final occurrence is
02208  *   the one that determines its value.
02209  *
02210  * Returns 0 on success and -1 on failure. On failure, the vector will be
02211  * unchanged. */
02212 static int Vector_swizzle_set(VectorObject *self, PyObject *value, void *closure)
02213 {
02214     size_t size_from;
02215     float scalarVal;
02216 
02217     size_t axis_from;
02218     size_t axis_to;
02219 
02220     unsigned int swizzleClosure;
02221 
02222     float tvec[MAX_DIMENSIONS];
02223     float vec_assign[MAX_DIMENSIONS];
02224 
02225     if (BaseMath_ReadCallback(self) == -1)
02226         return -1;
02227 
02228     /* Check that the closure can be used with this vector: even 2D vectors have
02229      * swizzles defined for axes z and w, but they would be invalid. */
02230     swizzleClosure = GET_INT_FROM_POINTER(closure);
02231     axis_from = 0;
02232 
02233     while (swizzleClosure & SWIZZLE_VALID_AXIS) {
02234         axis_to = swizzleClosure & SWIZZLE_AXIS;
02235         if (axis_to >= self->size) {
02236             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError,
02237                             "Vector swizzle: "
02238                             "specified axis not present");
02239             return -1;
02240         }
02241         swizzleClosure = swizzleClosure >> SWIZZLE_BITS_PER_AXIS;
02242         axis_from++;
02243     }
02244 
02245     if (((scalarVal = PyFloat_AsDouble(value)) == -1 && PyErr_Occurred()) == 0) {
02246         int i;
02247 
02248         for (i = 0; i < MAX_DIMENSIONS; i++) {
02249             vec_assign[i] = scalarVal;
02250         }
02251 
02252         size_from = axis_from;
02253     }
02254     else if ((PyErr_Clear()), /* run but ignore the result */
02255              (size_from = mathutils_array_parse(vec_assign, 2, 4, value,
02256                                                 "mathutils.Vector.**** = swizzle assignment")) == -1)
02257     {
02258         return -1;
02259     }
02260 
02261     if (axis_from != size_from) {
02262         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError,
02263                         "Vector swizzle: size does not match swizzle");
02264         return -1;
02265     }
02266 
02267     /* Copy vector contents onto swizzled axes. */
02268     axis_from = 0;
02269     swizzleClosure = GET_INT_FROM_POINTER(closure);
02270 
02271     while (swizzleClosure & SWIZZLE_VALID_AXIS) {
02272         axis_to = swizzleClosure & SWIZZLE_AXIS;
02273         tvec[axis_to] = vec_assign[axis_from];
02274         swizzleClosure = swizzleClosure >> SWIZZLE_BITS_PER_AXIS;
02275         axis_from++;
02276     }
02277 
02278     memcpy(self->vec, tvec, axis_from * sizeof(float));
02279     /* continue with BaseMathObject_WriteCallback at the end */
02280 
02281     if (BaseMath_WriteCallback(self) == -1)
02282         return -1;
02283     else
02284         return 0;
02285 }

02682 /* ROW VECTOR Multiplication - Vector X Matrix
02683  * [x][y][z] * [1][4][7]
02684  *             [2][5][8]
02685  *             [3][6][9]
02686  * vector/matrix multiplication IS NOT COMMUTATIVE!!!! */
02687 static int row_vector_multiplication(float r_vec[MAX_DIMENSIONS], VectorObject *vec, MatrixObject *mat)
02688 {
02689     float vec_cpy[MAX_DIMENSIONS];
02690     int row, col, z = 0, vec_size = vec->size;
02691 
02692     if (mat->num_row != vec_size) {
02693         if (mat->num_row == 4 && vec_size == 3) {
02694             vec_cpy[3] = 1.0f;
02695         }
02696         else {
02697             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
02698                             "vector * matrix: matrix column size "
02699                             "and the vector size must be the same");
02700             return -1;
02701         }
02702     }
02703 
02704     if (BaseMath_ReadCallback(vec) == -1 || BaseMath_ReadCallback(mat) == -1)
02705         return -1;
02706 
02707     memcpy(vec_cpy, vec->vec, vec_size * sizeof(float));
02708 
02709     r_vec[3] = 1.0f;
02710     //muliplication
02711     for (col = 0; col < mat->num_col; col++) {
02712         double dot = 0.0;
02713         for (row = 0; row < mat->num_row; row++) {
02714             dot += MATRIX_ITEM(mat, row, col) * vec_cpy[row];
02715         }
02716         r_vec[z++] = (float)dot;
02717     }
02718     return 0;
02719 }

02874  * pass Py_WRAP - if vector is a WRAPPER for data allocated by BLENDER
02875  * (i.e. it was allocated elsewhere by MEM_mallocN())
02876  *  pass Py_NEW - if vector is not a WRAPPER and managed by PYTHON
02877  * (i.e. it must be created here with PyMEM_malloc())*/
02878 PyObject *Vector_CreatePyObject(float *vec, const int size, const int type, PyTypeObject *base_type)
02879 {
02880     VectorObject *self;
02881 
02882     if (size < 2) {
02883         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError,
02884                         "Vector(): invalid size");
02885         return NULL;
02886     }
02887 
02888     self = base_type ? (VectorObject *)base_type->tp_alloc(base_type, 0) :
02889                        (VectorObject *)PyObject_GC_New(VectorObject, &vector_Type);
02890 
02891     if (self) {
02892         self->size = size;
02893 
02894         /* init callbacks as NULL */
02895         self->cb_user = NULL;
02896         self->cb_type = self->cb_subtype = 0;
02897 
02898         if (type == Py_WRAP) {
02899             self->vec = vec;
02900             self->wrapped = Py_WRAP;
02901         }
02902         else if (type == Py_NEW) {
02903             self->vec = PyMem_Malloc(size * sizeof(float));
02904             if (vec) {
02905                 memcpy(self->vec, vec, size * sizeof(float));
02906             }
02907             else { /* new empty */
02908                 fill_vn_fl(self->vec, size, 0.0f);
02909                 if (size == 4) { /* do the homogenous thing */
02910                     self->vec[3] = 1.0f;
02911                 }
02912             }
02913             self->wrapped = Py_NEW;
02914         }
02915         else {
02916             Py_FatalError("Vector(): invalid type!");
02917         }
02918     }
02919     return (PyObject *) self;
02920 }
